### Volunteers, drop-ins and MS Teams support

We have different groups of volunteers to support you with your projects. We have:

-   Technical volunteers who will support through the [Pre-stats awayday hackathon group](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/team/19%3AmDwTrFC1t5hhuDsXfajF516hmOWTFGjgIvJcPjdCLNM1%40thread.tacv2/conversations?groupId=620ed7ec-9dc9-4ca1-bc7b-848f6bd80878&tenantId=fad277c9-c60a-4da1-b5f3-b3b8b34a82f9) on Teams and [Drop-in sessions](#drop-in-sessions)
-   Data / subject expert volunteers who will support through the [Pre-stats awayday hackathon group](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/team/19%3AmDwTrFC1t5hhuDsXfajF516hmOWTFGjgIvJcPjdCLNM1%40thread.tacv2/conversations?groupId=620ed7ec-9dc9-4ca1-bc7b-848f6bd80878&tenantId=fad277c9-c60a-4da1-b5f3-b3b8b34a82f9) on Teams. This does not apply to all projects.

::: callout-important
Our lead volunteers might not be able to respond to your message right away, as they could be assisting someone else. Try to get in touch with the supporting volunteers in these cases. We really appreciate your patience and kindness while waiting for a reply!
:::

#### Data / subject expert volunteers

-   If there is a data expert volunteer for your project, you can find out more information about them in the [Support for data background about the project section](#data-background) of this document.

-   You can contact them through the [Pre-stats awayday hackathon group](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/team/19%3AmDwTrFC1t5hhuDsXfajF516hmOWTFGjgIvJcPjdCLNM1%40thread.tacv2/conversations?groupId=620ed7ec-9dc9-4ca1-bc7b-848f6bd80878&tenantId=fad277c9-c60a-4da1-b5f3-b3b8b34a82f9) on Teams or by dropping them a message.

-   Otherwise, please use the documentation provided to find out the information you need about the data.

#### Technical volunteers

##### Drop-in sessions {#drop-in-sessions}

Our technical volunteers are running drop-in sessions for the technical aspects of the projects. You can find the MS Teams link for the drop-in sessions and more information in the [agenda section](#agenda).

##### MS Teams support

::: callout-tip
Use '\@' to tag the relevant volunteers from the table below so they can spot your questions faster. We also encourage you to help each other out in the channel.
:::

If you need help with your project outside of the drop-in sessions, you can:

1.  Go to the [Pre-stats awayday hackathon group](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/team/19%3AmDwTrFC1t5hhuDsXfajF516hmOWTFGjgIvJcPjdCLNM1%40thread.tacv2/conversations?groupId=620ed7ec-9dc9-4ca1-bc7b-848f6bd80878&tenantId=fad277c9-c60a-4da1-b5f3-b3b8b34a82f9) group on Teams.

2.  Use the MS Teams channel to ask questions and get help from the organisers and volunteers.

3.  Select the relevant channel for your query.

    -   For example, we have a channel dedicated to RShiny where you can post all your RShiny related questions.

4.  Provide the following so the volunteers can help you:

    -   Your project name
    -   A summary of the issue you are facing
    -   Any error messages you are getting
    -   [Minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example) to recreate your error if applicable


